Rule: Having a Bachelor's degree increases the probability of earning more than $50k.
Being Self-Employed increases the probability of earning more than $50k.
Marital status can influence income, but the effect is complex and may depend on other factors.
Occupations in White-Collar or Professional fields increase the probability of earning more than $50k.
Both very high and very low working hours can be associated with higher incomes.
Older age, indicating more experience, can be a positive factor.
Obtaining a higher level of education (such as a Doctorate) significantly impacts income positively.
Combining higher education, a change in occupation, and a change in workclass leads to a positive outcome.
